    },
    "notes": [
      {
        "text": "An authenticated developer user can utilize webMethods Integration Server to create a user through the scheduler service and then elevate that user to an administrator using runAsUser. This action provides elevated privileges for the developer user. webMethods Integration Server could potentially allow an authenticated developer user to write an OSCommand.cnf file and then execute arbitrary commands on the server. webMethods Integration Server may also allow an authenticated developer to read /../.. files, even after checkFileRead is set.",
        "title": "Risk Evaluation",
        "category": "summary"
      },
